<h3 id="è‡ªåŠ¨æ¨ç†">è‡ªåŠ¨æ¨ç†</h3>

<blockquote>
  <p>Automated reasoning is an area of computer science dedicated to understanding different aspects of reasoning. The study of automated reasoning helps produce computer programs that allow computers to reason completely, or nearly completely, automatically. The most developed subareas of automated reasoning are <strong>automated theorem proving</strong> (and the less automated but more pragmatic subfield of interactive theorem proving) and <strong>automated proof checking</strong> (viewed as guaranteed correct reasoning under fixed assumptions).</p>
</blockquote>

<p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Certified-Programming-Dependent-Types-Introduction/dp/0262026651/ref=sr_1_fkmrnull_1?keywords=Certified+Programming+with+Dependent+Types&amp;qid=1555168397&amp;s=books&amp;sr=1-1-fkmrnull"><strong>Certified Programming with Dependent Types (CPDT)</strong></a>, 2019, Adam Chlipala</p>

