  <li><strong>æ¶‰åŠè¯é¢˜:</strong> formal logic notation, proof methods; induction, well-ordering; sets, relations; elementary graph theory; integer congruences; asymptotic notation and growth of functions; permutations and combinations, counting principles; discrete probability. Further selected æ¶‰åŠè¯é¢˜ may also be covered, such as recursive definition and structural induction; state machines and invariants; recurrences; generating functions.</li>
