<p><a href="https://www.logicmatters.net/categories/"><strong>Category Theory: A Gentle Introduction</strong></a>, Peter Smith</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>é€‚ç”¨äººç¾¤:</strong> <em>undergraduates</em></li>
  <li>This Gentle Introduction is very much still work in progress, so there are chapters at different levels of development and with different degrees of integration with whatâ€™s around them. So far, at least in a rough and ready way, we cover the basic notions of <strong>elementary category theory</strong> â€“ explaining the very idea of a category, then treating limits, functors, natural transformations, representables, adjunctions. The long-term plan is (possibly) to say something about categorial logic, explore categories of sets, and even edge towards some initial themes in topos theory</li>
  <li>Free PDF Copy: https://www.logicmatters.net/resources/pdfs/GentleIntro.pdf</li>
